    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion<strong> </strong>has softened, add your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>drained macaroni</strong>,<strong> drained sweetcorn</strong>,<strong> creamy single soy</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, then cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, take the pan off the heat and stir in the<strong> grated cheeze</strong>, then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>smoky chipotle mac ‘n’ cheeze</strong></p>",
